Good point — dotCMS expects the relationship value to be an array of identifiers even for a single item. Let me check the current code — it already splits by comma into an array:

```javascript
var ids = mf.value.split(',').map(function (id) { return id.trim(); }).filter(function (id) { return id; });
relationships[velVar] = ids;
```

So `relationships[velVar]` is already an array. The payload will look like:

```json
{
  "contentlet": {
    "contentType": "Blog",
    "relationships": {
      "BlogAuthor.blog": ["abc-123-def"]
    }
  }
}
```

